<subsection xml:id="subsec-Constructing-triangles">
        <title>Constructing triangles</title>
                    <p>
                    A triangle is a basic shape with three sides and three angles. The three sides of a triangle can have different lengths, and the angles can vary in size, but the sum of the angles in any triangle is always  <m>180^\circ</m>.    
                    </p>
                        <figure>
                            <caption>Determine whether three segments can form a triangle</caption>
                            <interactive xml:id="triangle" geogebra="vtgbmpak" width="100%" aspect="9:5" reset-icon="yes" />
                        </figure>
                    <p>
                        Types of Triangles
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Triangles can be classified based on angles and sides. 
                    </p>
                                           
                    <p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Scalene Triangle.
                                </p>
                            </li>

                            <li>
                                <p>
                                Equilateral Triangle. 
